The command was incorrect for Windows. Here are the correct Azure CLI installation methods for different terminals:

ğŸ–¥ï¸ AZURE CLI INSTALLATION BY TERMINAL
Windows PowerShell (Recommended)
powershell
# Run PowerShell as Administrator
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri https://aka.ms/installazurecliwindows -OutFile AzureCLI.msi
Start-Process msiexec.exe -Wait -ArgumentList '/I AzureCLI.msi /quiet'
Windows Command Prompt (cmd)
cmd
# Run as Administrator
curl -L https://aka.ms/installazurecliwindows -o AzureCLI.msi
msiexec /I AzureCLI.msi /quiet
Windows Terminal (Modern)
powershell
# Windows Terminal uses PowerShell by default
# Same as PowerShell commands above
winget install Microsoft.AzureCLI
Git Bash (If you have Git for Windows)
bash
# Git Bash on Windows
curl -L https://aka.ms/installazurecliwindows -o AzureCLI.msi
./AzureCLI.msi
WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)
bash
# If you have WSL installed
curl -sL https://aka.ms/InstallAzureCLIDeb | sudo bash
ğŸ¯ RECOMMENDED FOR YOU
