The original command was for Linux/Ubuntu, which is why it wouldn't work on your Windows mini PC. The corrected commands above are specifically for Windows environments.

Feedback submitted



acesss to path is denied
The "access to path is denied" error means you need to run PowerShell as Administrator. Here's how to fix this:

ğŸ”§ SOLUTION - RUN AS ADMINISTRATOR
Method 1: PowerShell as Administrator
Press Windows Key + X
Select "Windows PowerShell (Admin)" or "Terminal (Admin)"
Click "Yes" when UAC prompt appears
Run the installation command:
powershell
# Now with admin privileges
winget install Microsoft.AzureCLI
Method 2: Windows Terminal as Admin
Open Windows Terminal
Right-click on the Terminal icon in taskbar
Select "Run as administrator"
Click "Yes" on UAC prompt
Run the command:
powershell
winget install Microsoft.AzureCLI
Method 3: Manual Download (No Admin Required)
If you can't get admin rights, use this alternative:

Download directly: https://aka.ms/installazurecliwindows
Double-click the downloaded MSI file
Follow the installation wizard
Restart PowerShell/terminal
Method 4: Chocolatey (If installed)
powershell
# If you have Chocolatey package manager
choco install azure-cli
ğŸ” VERIFY ADMIN ACCESS
To check if you're running as administrator:

powershell
# This should show "True" if you're admin
([Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal][Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).IsInRole([Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)
ğŸ¯ QUICK FIX
The easiest solution is:

Right-click Start button
Choose "PowerShell (Admin)"
Run this command:
powershell
winget install Microsoft.AzureCLI
After installation, restart PowerShell and verify:

powershell
az --version
az login
The "access denied" error happens because Azure CLI needs to install system files, which requires administrator privileges on Windows.

